<p>In <code>package.json</code> I have:</p>  <pre><code>"preferences": [{     "name": "hotkeyPopup",     "title": "Hotkey for translating selected text",     "type": "string",     "value": "alt-Y"   }] </code></pre>  <p>And it looks like <code>input type=text</code>. How can I capture user's hotkey combination? This is not cool that user must type by hands words like <code>alt</code> or even worse <code>accel</code>.</p>  <p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/Add-ons/SDK/High-Level_APIs/hotkeys" rel="nofollow">Official documentation about hotkeys</a> say nothing about capturing in preferences.</p>